HEADWORD: Calcarated
<hw>Cal"ca*ra`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>calcaratus</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>calcar</ets>. See 2d <ets>Calcar</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having a spur, as the flower of
the toadflax and larkspur; spurred.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Armed with a spur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calcareo-argillaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
